  "text": "The Tucson study [CITATION_1] found an association with cardiac defects, but this finding conflicted with the findings in the Woburn and northern New Jersey studies. However, the Woburn study did find a cluster of choanal atresia, a defect related to conotruncal heart defects. The Woburn and northern New Jersey studies found similar associations with NTDs and cleft lip. In addition, the Woburn study found an association with eye defects.",
